{"Name":"Vibrate Plugin","Id":1517,"Alias":"VibratePlugin","Description":"# Vibrate Plugin Details\r\n\r\n\r\nSimple but elegant way of performing Vibrate in your Xamarin.iOS, Xamarin.Android, PCL, Windows, and Xamarin.Forms projects.\r\n\r\nWorks completely from shared code or PCL projects.","Version":"1.0.0.5","Summary":"Easily access the vibrate feature of any device.","QuickStart":"# Getting Started with Vibrate Plugin\r\n\r\n**ANDROID Specific**\r\nPlease ensure you have the VIBRATE persmission enabled:\r\n\r\n```\r\n\u003cuses-permission android:name=\"android.permission.VIBRATE\" /\u003e\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### API Usage\r\n\r\nTo gain access to the Vibrate class simply use this method:\r\n\r\n```\r\nvar v = CrossVibrate.Current;\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Methods\r\n\r\n```\r\n CrossVibrate.Current.Vibrate(int milliseconds = 500);\r\n```\r\n\r\nVibrate device for specified amount of time. 500 is the default and will vibrate for 500 milliseconds.\r\n\r\n**iOS Specific**\r\nThere is no API to vibrate for a specific amount of time, so it will vibrate for the default no matter what.\r\n","Hash":"a68e9798c86e4ebb63a8bd9765cc175a","TargetPlatforms":["ios","android"],"TrialHash":null}